    "synopsis": {
        "native": "Documental narrado por Cecilia Roth y con la participaci\u00f3n de los supervivientes de la m\u00edtica banda de rock Tequila, Ariel Rot, Alejo Stivel y Felipe Lipe. Cuenta la historia del legendario grupo de rock que puso la banda sonora a la liberaci\u00f3n de los j\u00f3venes espa\u00f1oles en la transici\u00f3n. Cinco j\u00f3venes que alcanzaron de golpe su sue\u00f1o de triunfo y a los que la fama y el \u00e9xito les destruy\u00f3. Pero sus canciones han logrado perdurar en el tiempo como cl\u00e1sicos indestructibles.",
        "english": "\"Tequila. Sexo, Drogas y Rock and Roll\" is a documentary that tells the story of the legendary Spanish rock band who provided the soundtrack for the liberation of young people during The Spanish Transition between the late 70s to the early 80s. Five young people whose turned in the Spanish Rolling Stones whose suddenly pull off their dream of making good music but that they were destroyed by the incredible fame and success they reached. Although their songs have succeeded in lasting over time as indestructible classics for the later generations as well as new legions of fans."
    },
